Remarks.
Despite some minor differences in general appearance of individuals from different populations (
Figs. 68–91
), their body proportions are rather close (
Table 1
). Male genitalia structure is stable in all populations studied (
Figs. 109–114
). Only one population from Racha Mountain Range (Mravaldzali vicinity) comprises black individuals. The upper side is usually with metallic luster, but generally more matt than in the nominotypical subspecies, bronze to blue.
